### Pool API Test Cases
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000/api/v1

### 1. Login as super admin to get token
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "superadmin@example.com",
  "password": "SuperAdmin@123"
}

### 2. Get all sample products (to get a category ID for pool creation)
GET {{host}}/sample-products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Create a new pool
POST {{host}}/pools
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Premium Whey Protein Pool",
  "categoryId": "{{sample_product_id}}",
  "sampleSource": "Lab Testing Facility A",
  "batchNumber": "BATCH-001-2024",
  "description": "High-quality protein sample for laboratory analysis",
  "poolPrice": 99.99
}

### 4. Get all pools
GET {{host}}/pools
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get my pools (pools created by current user)
GET {{host}}/pools/my-pools
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get a specific pool by ID
GET {{host}}/pools/{{pool_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Update a pool
PUT {{host}}/pools/{{pool_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Premium Whey Protein Pool",
  "description": "Updated high-quality protein sample for laboratory analysis",
  "poolPrice": 129.99
}

### 8. Approve a pool (admin only)
PUT {{host}}/pools/{{pool_id}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Get all pools including unapproved (to see the approved status)
GET {{host}}/pools?includeUnapproved=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Soft delete a pool
DELETE {{host}}/pools/{{pool_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Restore a deleted pool (admin only)
PUT {{host}}/pools/{{pool_id}}/restore
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Variables (replace these with actual values from responses)
@host = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@token = your_jwt_token_here
@sample_product_id = your_sample_product_id_here
@pool_id = your_pool_id_here